From 85976aedba6c7a30d4231c163814e04ad1d49b6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: User-3090 <71881005+User-3090@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 08:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/8] fix(windows): transport host colors safely

Query host foreground and background colors on Windows, preserve complete
OSC replies across the console input backends, and carry color and appearance
events to the server as structured input. Bound interrupted or unterminated
host replies so their tails cannot become pane input.

This adds client-input wire variants, so advance the protocol from the latest
released value 17 to 18 and refresh the checked-in API schema protocol value.

Fork-Ref: 006886c96c9f98f4056894d5da402b22188e79fc; f3fac551ece1b3f05276bb60f33ed16fbd487f70
